{"title_page": "+TVI", "text_new": "{{Infobox TV channel\n| name=+TVI\n| logosize=200px\n| logofile=+TVI logo.png\n| launch            = {{Start date and age|2013|1|25}}\n| closed date       = {{End date and age|2015|12|1}}\n| slogan= \n| owner= [[Televis\u00e3o Independente|TVI]] ([[Media Capital]])\n| sister names     = [[TVI (Portugal)|TVI]]<br/>[[TVI Fic\u00e7\u00e3o]]<br/>[[TVI 24]]<br/>[[TVI Internacional]]<br/>[[Televis\u00e3o Independente|TVI]]\n| picture format   = [[16:9]]/[[4:3]] ([[576i]], [[SDTV]])\n| share            = \n| share as of      = \n| share source     = \n| web=[http://www.maistvi.com Mais TVI]\n| country          = [[Portugal]]\n| broadcast area   = [[Portugal]]<br/>[[Angola]]<br/>[[Mozambique]]\n| sat serv 1       = [[NOS (Portuguese media company)|NOS]]\n| sat chan 1       = 74\n| sat serv 2       = \n| sat chan 2       = \n| sat serv 3       = ZAP <small>[[Angola|ao]]</small>\n| sat chan 3       = 75\n| sat serv 4       = ZAP <small>[[Mozambique|mz]]</small>\n| sat chan 4       = 75\n| cable serv 1     = [[NOS (Portuguese media company)|NOS]]\n| cable chan 1     = 74\n| cable serv 2     = \n| cable chan 2     = \n| cable serv 3     = TV Cabo <small>[[Angola|ao]]</small>\n| cable chan 3     = 75\n| cable serv 4     = TV Cabo <small>[[Mozambique|mz]]</small>\n| cable chan 4     = 75\n| adsl serv 1      = \n| adsl chan 1      = \n| adsl serv 2      = [[Vodafone Portugal]]\n| adsl chan 2      = 7\n| adsl serv 3      = \n| adsl chan 3      = \n}}\n\n'''Mais TVI''' (stylized as '''+TVI''') was a [[Portugal|Portuguese]] [[cable television|digital cable]] and [[satellite television|satellite]] [[television channel]] owned by [[TVI (Portugal)|TVI]]. The channel provided entertainment programming including TVI originals and international talk-shows.\n\nThe channel appeared after an agreement between TVI and [[NOS (Portuguese media company)|NOS]], formerly named ZON, on August 1, 2012. In Portugal it has an exclusivity contract with NOS television services, in a similar manner to its sister channel [[TVI Fic\u00e7\u00e3o]] with [[Meo (Portugal)|MEO]]. Both channels carry distinct programming.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.cmjornal.xl.pt/detalhe/noticias/ultima-hora/-tvi-chega-a-zon-ate-ao-final-do-ano |title=+ TVI chega \u00e0 Zon at\u00e9 ao final do ano - cmjornal.pt |access-date=2014-10-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140522213132/http://www.cmjornal.xl.pt/detalhe/noticias/ultima-hora/-tvi-chega-a-zon-ate-ao-final-do-ano |archive-date=2014-05-22 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.cmjornal.xl.pt/detalhe/noticias/lazer/tv--media/entretenimento-da-tvi-fica-na-zon |title=cmjornal.pt |access-date=2014-10-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140522213432/http://www.cmjornal.xl.pt/detalhe/noticias/lazer/tv--media/entretenimento-da-tvi-fica-na-zon |archive-date=2014-05-22 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n\nThe channel ended its broadcast on December 1, 2015, with a NOS test card (featuring sound from the Brazilian TV show ''P\u00e2nico na Band'', that was broadcasting due to automated continuity).\n\n== History ==\n\n=== Partnership between TVI and NOS ===\nOn August 1, 2012, +TVI and [[NOS (Portuguese media company)|NOS]] (formerly ZON) signed a partnership to launch +TVI. It was signed by Rodrigo Costa, ZON's president and [[Media Capital]]'s CEO Rosa Cullell. It was revealed that the channel would have a post-summer launch and that it would be broadcast in high definition, none of which happened at the time.\n\nThe channel was closed on December 1, 2015, due to the launch of another NOS exclusive TVI channel, TVI Reality, according to Media Capital's communications director Helena Forjaz.\n\nThe channel kept its exclusivity to its last day.\n\n== Shows ==\n\n=== Exclusive shows ===\n*''On Rec'' with [[Paulo Vint\u00e9m]]\n*''Tropa do Humor'' with Jo\u00e3o Pedro Santos\n*''Dan\u00e7a Com As Estrelas'' - backstage with [[Rita Pereira (actress)|Rita Pereira]]\n*''Pancas da Semana'' - with Alexandre Santos and NTS\n\n=== Discontinued exclusive shows ===\n\n*''Spot +'' with Iva Domingues\n* ''\u00c9 a Vida, Alvim!'' with Fernando Alvim\n* ''Video Pop'' with [[Leonor Poeiras]] and Nuno Eir\u00f3\n* ''Tu C\u00e1 Tu L\u00e1'' with [[Manuel Lu\u00eds Goucha]]\n* ''Vox \u2013 Em Busca da Com\u00e9dia'' with Carlos Moura\n\n=== Other shows ===\n\n* ''A Tua Cara N\u00e3o Me \u00c9 Estranha'' - backstage\n* ''Guestlist''\n* ''Fotografia Total''\n* ''Take Off''\n\n=== International Shows ===\n\n* ''[[101 Ways to Leave a Gameshow]]''\n* ''[[Love in the Wild]]''\n* ''[[Wipeout (2008 U.S. game show)|Wipeout]]''\n* ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon|The Tonight Show with Jimmy Fallon]]''\n* ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]''\n* ''[[Excused]]''\n* ''ET - Entretenimento Total''\n* ''ABC do Sexo''\n* ''OBESOS - A Transforma\u00e7\u00e3o Extrema''\n* ''[[The Insider (TV program)|The Insider]]''\n* ''[[P\u00e2nico na Band]]''\n* ''[[The Block (Australian TV series)|The Block]]''\n* ''[[Comedy Central Roast]]''\n\n=== TVI replays ===\n\n* ''Perdidos na Tribo''\n* ''Fear Factor - Desafio Total''\n* ''[[Uma Can\u00e7\u00e3o para Ti (Portugal)|Uma Can\u00e7\u00e3o para Ti]]''\n* ''A Tua Cara n\u00e3o me \u00e9 Estranha''\n* ''[[Big Brother (Portuguese TV series)|Big Brother]]''\n* ''Melhor do que Falecer''\n\n=== Episodes ===\n\n* ''Ele \u00e9 Ela''\n* ''Ol\u00e1 Pai!''\n* ''Destino Imortal''\n* ''37''\n* ''O Dom''\n* ''Reden\u00e7\u00e3o''\n* ''O Amor \u00e9 um Sonho''\n* ''Dias Felizes''\n* ''Crian\u00e7as S.O.S''\n* ''Clube das Chaves''\n* ''O Bando dos Quatro''\n* ''Campe\u00f5es e Detectives''\n* ''Detetive Maravilhas''\n* ''[[Morangos com A\u00e7\u00facar]] (3rd-9th seasons)''\n\n=== Special broadcasts ===\n\n* ''Festa de Lan\u00e7amento +TVI''\n* ''Concerto I Heart Radio Music''\n* NOS Air Race Championship\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Portuguese television stations}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mais TVI}}\n[[Category:Defunct television channels in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 2013]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations disestablished in 2015]]\n[[Category:2013 establishments in Portugal]]\n[[Category:2015 disestablishments in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Televis\u00e3o Independente]]\n\n\n{{Europe-tv-station-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox TV channel\n| name=+TVI\n| logosize=200px\n| logofile=+TVI logo.png\n| launch            = {{Start date and age|2013|1|25}}\n| closed date       = {{End date and age|2015|12|1}}\n| slogan= \n| owner= [[Televis\u00e3o Independente|TVI]] ([[Media Capital]])\n| sister names     = [[TVI (Portugal)|TVI]]<br/>[[TVI Fic\u00e7\u00e3o]]<br/>[[TVI 24]]<br/>[[TVI Internacional]]<br/>[[Televis\u00e3o Independente|TVI]]\n| picture format   = [[16:9]]/[[4:3]] ([[576i]], [[SDTV]])\n| share            = \n| share as of      = \n| share source     = \n| web=[http://www.maistvi.com Mais TVI]\n| country          = [[Portugal]]\n| broadcast area   = [[Portugal]]<br/>[[Angola]]<br/>[[Mozambique]]\n| sat serv 1       = [[NOS (Portuguese media company)|NOS]]\n| sat chan 1       = 74\n| sat serv 2       = \n| sat chan 2       = \n| sat serv 3       = ZAP <small>[[Angola|ao]]</small>\n| sat chan 3       = 75\n| sat serv 4       = ZAP <small>[[Mozambique|mz]]</small>\n| sat chan 4       = 75\n| cable serv 1     = [[NOS (Portuguese media company)|NOS]]\n| cable chan 1     = 74\n| cable serv 2     = \n| cable chan 2     = \n| cable serv 3     = TV Cabo <small>[[Angola|ao]]</small>\n| cable chan 3     = 75\n| cable serv 4     = TV Cabo <small>[[Mozambique|mz]]</small>\n| cable chan 4     = 75\n| adsl serv 1      = \n| adsl chan 1      = \n| adsl serv 2      = [[Vodafone Portugal]]\n| adsl chan 2      = 7\n| adsl serv 3      = \n| adsl chan 3      = \n}}\n\n'''Mais TVI''' (stylized as '''+TVI''') was a [[Portugal|Portuguese]] [[cable television|digital cable]] and [[satellite television|satellite]] [[television channel]] owned by [[TVI (Portugal)|TVI]]. The channel provided entertainment programming including TVI originals and international talk-shows.\n\nThe channel appeared after an agreement between TVI and [[NOS (Portuguese media company)|NOS]], formerly named ZON, on August 1, 2012. In Portugal it has an exclusivity contract with NOS television services, in a similar manner to its sister channel [[TVI Fic\u00e7\u00e3o]] with [[Meo (Portugal)|MEO]]. Both channels carry distinct programming.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.cmjornal.xl.pt/detalhe/noticias/ultima-hora/-tvi-chega-a-zon-ate-ao-final-do-ano |title=+ TVI chega \u00e0 Zon at\u00e9 ao final do ano - cmjornal.pt |access-date=2014-10-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140522213132/http://www.cmjornal.xl.pt/detalhe/noticias/ultima-hora/-tvi-chega-a-zon-ate-ao-final-do-ano |archive-date=2014-05-22 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.cmjornal.xl.pt/detalhe/noticias/lazer/tv--media/entretenimento-da-tvi-fica-na-zon |title=cmjornal.pt |access-date=2014-10-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140522213432/http://www.cmjornal.xl.pt/detalhe/noticias/lazer/tv--media/entretenimento-da-tvi-fica-na-zon |archive-date=2014-05-22 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n\nThe channel ended its broadcast on December 1, 2015, with a NOS test card (featuring sound from the Brazilian TV show ''P\u00e2nico na Band'', that was broadcasting due to automated continuity).\n\n== History ==\n\n=== Partnership between TVI and NOS ===\nOn August 1, 2012, +TVI and [[NOS (Portuguese media company)|NOS]] (formerly ZON) signed a partnership to launch +TVI. It was signed by Rodrigo Costa, ZON's president and [[Media Capital]]'s CEO Rosa Cullell. It was revealed that the channel would have a post-summer launch and that it would be broadcast in high definition, none of which happened at the time.\n\nThe channel was closed on December 1, 2015, due to the launch of another NOS exclusive TVI channel, TVI Reality, according to Media Capital's communications director Helena Forjaz.\n\nThe channel kept its exclusivity to its last day.\n\n== Shows ==\n\n=== Exclusive shows ===\n*''On Rec'' with [[Paulo Vint\u00e9m]]\n*<i aria-labelledby=\"23x15px&amp;#124;border_&amp;#124;alt=Portugal&amp;#124;link=Portugal_Television_in_Portugal\">Tropa do Humor</i> with Jo\u00e3o Pedro Santos\n*Dan\u00e7a Com As Estrelas - backstage with [[Rita Pereira (actress)|Rita Pereira]]\n*Pancas da Semana - with Alexandre Santos and NTS\n\n=== Discontinued exclusive shows ===\n\n*''Spot +'' with Iva Domingues\n* ''\u00c9 a Vida, Alvim!'' with Fernando Alvim\n* ''Video Pop'' with [[Leonor Poeiras]] and Nuno Eir\u00f3\n* ''Tu C\u00e1 Tu L\u00e1'' with [[Manuel Lu\u00eds Goucha]]\n* ''Vox \u2013 Em Busca da Com\u00e9dia'' with Carlos Moura\n\n=== Other shows ===\n\n* ''A Tua Cara N\u00e3o Me \u00c9 Estranha'' - backstage\n* ''Guestlist''\n* ''Fotografia Total''\n* ''Take Off''\n\n=== International Shows ===\n\n* ''[[101 Ways to Leave a Gameshow]]''\n* ''[[Love in the Wild]]''\n* ''[[Wipeout (2008 U.S. game show)|Wipeout]]''\n* ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon|The Tonight Show with Jimmy Fallon]]''\n* ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]''\n* ''[[Excused]]''\n* ''ET - Entretenimento Total''\n* ''ABC do Sexo''\n* ''OBESOS - A Transforma\u00e7\u00e3o Extrema''\n* ''[[The Insider (TV program)|The Insider]]''\n* ''[[P\u00e2nico na Band]]''\n* ''[[The Block (Australian TV series)|The Block]]''\n* ''[[Comedy Central Roast]]''\n\n=== TVI replays ===\n\n* ''Perdidos na Tribo''\n* ''Fear Factor - Desafio Total''\n* ''[[Uma Can\u00e7\u00e3o para Ti (Portugal)|Uma Can\u00e7\u00e3o para Ti]]''\n* ''A Tua Cara n\u00e3o me \u00e9 Estranha''\n* ''[[Big Brother (Portuguese TV series)|Big Brother]]''\n* ''Melhor do que Falecer''\n\n=== Episodes ===\n\n* ''Ele \u00e9 Ela''\n* ''Ol\u00e1 Pai!''\n* ''Destino Imortal''\n* ''37''\n* ''O Dom''\n* ''Reden\u00e7\u00e3o''\n* ''O Amor \u00e9 um Sonho''\n* ''Dias Felizes''\n* ''Crian\u00e7as S.O.S''\n* ''Clube das Chave